# Scroll layout (StudySaver)

The app uses **document scrolling** on `html`, not a nested scroll container.

## Do NOT

- Set `overflow: hidden` on `html` or `body` (except onboarding routes that manage their own scroll)
- Wrap the app in `fixed inset-0 overflow-hidden` shells with inner scroll areas
- Add framer-motion page wrappers with `transform`/`translateY` around full pages (`app/(app)/template.tsx` must stay a passthrough)
- Use `min-h-[100dvh]` + `min-h-full` chains that trap content in viewport-height boxes
- Make charts/maps capture touch (`pointer-events-none` on Recharts wrappers)

## Do

- Keep `AppShell` as `<main className="pb-24">` + fixed bottom nav only
- Use `ScrollGuard` in `AppShell`; never leave `body.style.overflow` or `body.style.position` locked after modals/voice
- Put long page content in normal block flow; bottom nav clearance via `pb-24` on `main`
- After layout/CSS changes, verify home dashboard scrolls past Active Goal to Quick Actions in mobile emulation

## Dev note

Use `npm run dev` while iterating. If using `npm run start`, run `npm run build` first or you will test stale CSS.
